g.text: Kim Kitsuragi: "Three weeks maximum -- from the dust coverage. It could easily have been *one* week too. You know, officer..." He looks at you.
Footprints in the Dust: The dust has not settled again where these footprints have been made. The displacement in this dusty hell tells a story.
Empathy: This is so good it makes him forget the whole *Kimball* memory.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It means someone snuck through what seems like a secret route -- behind our rape victim's room. In the recent weeks. This may prove to be significant."
"It means someone snuck through what seems like a secret route -- behind Klaasje's room. In the recent weeks. This may prove to be significant."
You: This print doesn't look like the Odd Sole.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It means someone snuck through what seems like a *secret route* -- leading to the roof. The roof, from where you can *shoot* our victim. This is significant."
Footprints in the Dust: The footprints are of one type. They do not congratulate you for correctly recognizing what type they are not.
Empathy: This is good. He likes it. That's a little smile there -- in the dark of the workshop.
Footprints in the Dust: Large prints, most likely made by boots. The size is hard to determine (sole could be bigger than vamp). The soles have left a pattern -- uniform, horizontal lines.
Footprints in the Dust: Everything around you is quiet. The prints criss-cross the workshop floor.
Footprints in the Dust: The footprints are still there. They have told their story.
Footprints in the Dust: The footprints do not speak. They simply exist here, a product of the dust; just as the footprints outside are a product of the mud and apparently different shoes.
Kim Kitsuragi: "This isn't bad at all -- it was a *good* idea to see where that door leads. Commendable work bringing us to this place."
Visual Calculus: Shoe size is 41-42, maybe 43. It could be a large-footed woman or a small-to-average-footed man. This is, unfortunately, the worst, most vague shoe size there is.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It means someone snuck through what seems like a secret route -- behind our rape victim's room. In the recent weeks. This may prove to be significant."
"It means someone snuck through what seems like a secret route -- behind our rape victim's room. In the recent weeks. This may prove to be significant."
Kim Kitsuragi: "It was a *stereo-investigation* after all. It has now converged with our main investigation. Adding a new fact to *consider*."
Footprints in the Dust: You *clearly* see footprints in the downy carpet of dust covering the workshop floor.
Perception (Sight): One person has been here. They've gone back and forth. The tips point both ways.
Kim Kitsuragi: "It means someone snuck through what seems like a secret route -- leading to the roof. From where you can *shoot* our victim. This is significant."
Footprints in the Dust: Neither the footprints nor the dust speak their secrets. But you know: it means that someone has been back *here*.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Jackpot." The lieutenant takes out his notebook. "These, unlike everything else here, are *new*."
You: "This print doesn't look like the Odd-soled print we found at the hanging, Kim."
Encyclopedia: This print is unlike one left by a regular worker boot. It is not a *brand* sole, with logos on it. It seems custom made or old fashioned.

Kim Kitsuragi: "Between that," he points to the elevator doors in the corner, "and that," he points to the barred door.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I wouldn't rule out Ruby coming here yet. This isn't an argument against her. People change shoes, you know. But it's not argument *for* her either."
Kim Kitsuragi: "These prints, officer, could be the prints of our killer. And if not -- at least they're a good argument for this *Ruby* doing it. To present to Titus."
"Let's have a closer look then..." (Crouch, study the footprints.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "No. These little... horizontal lines are different. They look custom made to me. Or some kind of foreign print? Hard to say. Still a *boot* though."
You: "This doesn't look like the workers boots from the hanging, does it?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "The blue door was a *mega*-investigation after all -- it has now converged with our main investigation, which I would say is *quite* large."
Kim Kitsuragi: "These prints, officer -- could be the prints of our killer."
Kim Kitsuragi: He inspects the tracks closer. "The size looks about the same, actually. They're not the same *shoe*, but they *could* be the same person."
"Someone's been here -- within the last week or two."
You: One person went back and forth.
You: "The prints look like one person went back and forth."

Footprints in the Dust: The footprints go up the length of the room and back down. That is all they do.
